82. Lawter International Inc. - tribunedigital-chicagotribune




 



82. Lawter International Inc.May 15, 1994|By Profiled by the Chicago Tribune business reporting staff.990 Skokie Blvd., Northbrook 60062, 708-498-4700COMPANYFounded: 1940Year-end: Dec. 31.Employees: 537; 90 in IllinoisForeign sales: 45 percent of $172.2 millionStock: 365-day closeHigh: $15.50Low: $10.87April 29: $11.25May 1, 1994, value of $1,000 in company stockPurchased 1993: $828Purchased 1989: $1,806CHIEF EXECUTIVEDaniel J. Terra, 82, since 1958Cash compensation: NoneOptions granted: NoneOptions, stock appreciation rights exercised: NoneShares owned: 9,098,922 of 44.8 millionRestricted stock: NoneA new resin plant in Pleasant Prairie, Wis., will allow Lawter International to broaden its line of specialty chemicals used in printing inks, fluorescent pigments and coatings, paints, adhesives and rubber compounds. Lawter launched at least a dozen new products in 1993.Going global with a product line that includes environmentally friendly water-based inks is part of Lawter's strategy. The company has operations in more than a dozen countries.Analysts note that Lawter's 1993 earnings were about flat because of the tough economic climate in Europe, but they add that the Wisconsin plant will double the company's U.S. resin production capacity, boosting the bottom line. They add that Mexico is an attractive growth area, especially after adoption of the North American Free Trade Agreement.


